CRDB Bank Burundi is making significant strides after posting positive growth in profit and assets in the first five months of this year. The CRDB Burundi Managing Director, Mr Fredrick Siwale, said at Zanzibar President, Dr Hussein Mwinyiâ€™s meeting with Tanzanian investors in Burundi, that profit doubled to 4.38 million US dollars in first five months to May from 2.2 million US dollars in similar period last year. "We have consolidated our third position after leaping from fourth last year," Mr Siwale said at the meeting convened for Dr Mwinyi who had represented President Samia Suluhu Hassan at the celebration of 60 years of Burundi independence last Friday. CRDB Burundi which marks 10 years of operations in Bujumbura this October, has a capital of over 19 million US dollars compared to 13 million US dollars when it entered Bujumbura market in 2012. Mr Siwale the lender in Burundi facilitates the investments from both Tanzania and Burundi investors. "The strategy is creating a strong bank [in term of balance sheet and outreach] in Burundi similar to Tanzania," he said. The bank assets grew by 90 per cent to 500 million US dollars or 605 billion franc while deposits increased by 114 per cent to 175 million US dollars or 387 billion franc. Mr Siwale also said the amount of loan portfolio increased two-fold to 129 million US dollars or 264 billion franc at the end of May from 68 million US dollars or 139billion franc last May. The lenders what also to increase the number of bank agents from currently 600 to 1000 by the end of this year, aiming to taking the financial services close to the society. "We are targeting to raise Wakala numbers to 1000 and double super Wakala number [from 12 to 24] by the end of this year," Mr Siwale said. The Burundi subsidiary will also expand this year by opening a branch in Ngozi and next year opens branches at Gitega (the political capital), Makamba and Ruyigi townships.